01:45:54.000 --> 01:45:59.000
And somehow another, she kind of stuck.

01:45:59.000 --> 01:46:06.000
And then I looked around one day and I had an all my right side and all my left side.

01:46:06.000 --> 01:46:10.000
And she was just doing things.

01:46:10.000 --> 01:46:13.000
And we were just moving along and things were happening.

01:46:13.000 --> 01:46:16.000
She was useful.

01:46:16.000 --> 01:46:22.000
And then the next thing I knew, we were heading on out and I was headed to Atlanta.

01:46:22.000 --> 01:46:25.000
She was heading right with me.

01:46:25.000 --> 01:46:32.000
And then I think we went to Bill Hansen's wedding.

01:46:32.000 --> 01:46:35.000
And from there we went to Atlanta.

01:46:35.000 --> 01:46:41.000
And that's when she ran into the big folks.

01:46:41.000 --> 01:46:48.000
And then she stayed and then she, she been ever since.

01:46:48.000 --> 01:46:53.000
And not knowing that she could type like she did.

01:46:53.000 --> 01:46:54.000
No.

01:46:54.000 --> 01:46:59.000
Because they were looking for people to sit on that watch line when the reports came through.

01:46:59.000 --> 01:47:04.000
Somebody that could take it all down.

01:47:05.000 --> 01:47:10.000
I can't really say that I'm responsible for a little sis.

01:47:10.000 --> 01:47:15.000
She just happened to come along and latch on and we just went on through.

01:47:15.000 --> 01:47:17.000
What latch on to me?

01:47:17.000 --> 01:47:20.000
No, I can't think of anything.

01:47:20.000 --> 01:47:31.000
Well, it may be a few, but she was one that we just kind of bond it and went on.

01:47:31.000 --> 01:47:38.000
Well, (Chuck) McDew and I were very very close and Bob Moses Hansen and I were very close.

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:43.000
Trying to spell them in our very close.

01:47:43.000 --> 01:47:46.000
When did parents come in and pick you up?

